text.paragraph:
                         Digestive System—

Infrequent:abdominal distension, nausea and vomiting, tongue edema;

Rare: ileus, intestinal obstruction, liver fatty deposit.

                         Metabolic and Nutritional Disorders— 

frequent:alkaline phosphatase increased;

Infrequent:bilirubinemia, hypoproteinemia.

                         Nervous System—

Infrequent:ataxia, dysarthria, libido decreased, stupor;

Rare: coma.

                         Respiratory System—

Infrequent:epistaxis;

Rare: lung edema.

                         Special Senses—

Infrequent: abnormality of accommodation, dry eyes;

Rare: mydriasis.
